WEBVTT

01:26.550 --> 01:34.970
[LIVE UP TO YOUR YOUTH]

01:35.420 --> 01:37.950
[Episode 15]

01:39.070 --> 01:40.130
You care that much?

01:40.840 --> 01:42.190
Of course I care.

01:42.340 --> 01:44.270
I don't want you to misunderstand.

01:46.650 --> 01:49.009
Laugh if you want to.

01:49.070 --> 01:50.020
I don't want to.

01:56.710 --> 01:57.570
Then cry.

01:58.490 --> 01:59.430
Sit properly.

02:09.210 --> 02:11.740
The thing is,
that dish was really delicious.

02:12.560 --> 02:15.160
Not as delicious
as the food that girl brought.

02:16.790 --> 02:17.800
That girl and I—

02:17.810 --> 02:19.310
we really don't know each other.

02:19.310 --> 02:21.450
She just suddenly brought food over.

02:21.930 --> 02:22.460
Really.

02:22.480 --> 02:24.340
I didn't eat a single bite of her food.

02:24.340 --> 02:25.740
I told her to take it away.

02:25.800 --> 02:26.579
Who knows?

02:27.070 --> 02:28.400
What do you mean by that?

02:28.810 --> 02:30.530
Next time

02:30.840 --> 02:32.040
you bring me food,

02:32.340 --> 02:33.090
if you see that girl,

02:33.090 --> 02:34.030
I'll have her tell you.

02:34.030 --> 02:34.800
I'm not going.

02:34.800 --> 02:36.400
Let that girl bring it to you.

02:38.840 --> 02:39.370
Alright.

02:39.970 --> 02:40.829
Alright?

02:59.180 --> 03:00.410
Last time you came alone

03:00.410 --> 03:01.520
and asked me to arrange it for you.

03:01.520 --> 03:02.470
I did it for Director Weng's sake,

03:02.470 --> 03:03.280
didn't I?

03:03.360 --> 03:05.000
Now you brought all these outsiders here.

03:05.000 --> 03:06.190
Aren't you just being unreasonable?

03:06.190 --> 03:07.630
Our projection room
isn't open to the public.

03:07.630 --> 03:09.500
Not to mention
there are leaders here today.

03:09.500 --> 03:10.960
I can't help you with this.

03:11.310 --> 03:12.340
I just can't.

03:12.810 --> 03:13.840
Shengli. Shengli.

03:13.840 --> 03:14.280
We are not watching the movie.

03:14.280 --> 03:15.130
Call him out so we can beat him up.

03:15.130 --> 03:16.090
Let's just forget it.

03:16.090 --> 03:17.370
We shouldn't cause you any trouble.

03:17.370 --> 03:17.900
Exactly.

03:18.579 --> 03:19.910
Anyway,

03:20.030 --> 03:21.890
we still got to hang out together.

03:22.579 --> 03:23.620
Right, don't worry.

03:23.620 --> 03:24.810
If it doesn't work out,
you guys can watch.

03:24.810 --> 03:26.120
I'll take her on your new bike

03:26.120 --> 03:26.810
for a spin.

03:27.310 --> 03:27.960
A spin?

03:27.960 --> 03:28.900
You don't know the way. If you get lost,

03:28.900 --> 03:29.680
we'll have to go looking for you.

03:29.680 --> 03:30.060
Wait!

03:30.410 --> 03:30.860
Wait!

03:30.960 --> 03:31.560
What's up?

03:32.280 --> 03:33.079
I have an idea.

03:37.180 --> 03:38.020
Will it work?

03:38.430 --> 03:39.030
It will.

03:39.400 --> 03:40.060
Let's go up.

03:42.800 --> 03:43.500
We just want to watch a movie.

03:43.500 --> 03:45.030
Why are we sneaking around?

03:45.060 --> 03:45.680
Shut up.

03:45.710 --> 03:46.530
Will you die if you don't talk?

03:46.530 --> 03:48.210
I'll take you to buy the tickets. Come on.

03:48.210 --> 03:49.620
Hurry up. Come up here.

03:52.210 --> 03:53.960
Not even dating is this hard.

03:54.300 --> 03:55.230
What's going on?

03:57.120 --> 03:58.180
Hurry up.

03:58.210 --> 03:59.780
Don't make me late for the movie.

03:59.780 --> 04:00.560
How can a grown man

04:00.560 --> 04:01.810
-be afraid of heights?
-Are you scared or not?

04:01.810 --> 04:03.210
Don't talk so much
if your legs are shaking.

04:03.210 --> 04:04.300
I'm not scared.

04:04.340 --> 04:06.360
-Hurry up.
-Look how scared you are.

04:09.310 --> 04:10.110
Director.

04:10.810 --> 04:12.400
I think our script

04:12.470 --> 04:13.600
is better than this.

04:14.030 --> 04:15.430
If you were the director,

04:15.460 --> 04:17.190
it would definitely be better.

04:20.160 --> 04:21.519
This is a classic.

04:24.370 --> 04:28.650
[No Smoking]

04:55.500 --> 04:57.430
We can actually watch it from here?

05:34.640 --> 05:35.640
[The end]

05:37.970 --> 05:38.870
[The End]

05:40.390 --> 05:42.190
Why are there people in the back?

05:43.250 --> 05:43.909
Who are you?

05:44.270 --> 05:44.940
Come out!

05:45.510 --> 05:46.100
Staff!

05:46.180 --> 05:47.040
Go backstage quickly!

05:47.040 --> 05:47.720
Bye-bye!

05:47.720 --> 05:49.100
See ya!

05:51.390 --> 05:52.310
We should thank Mr. Xu

05:52.310 --> 05:53.500
for letting us

05:54.120 --> 05:55.570
watch the movie today.

05:56.480 --> 05:57.480
Thank you, Mr. Xu!

05:57.570 --> 05:58.690
-You're welcome.
-Thank you, Mr. Xu.

05:58.690 --> 06:00.610
Your sister always helps you

06:00.660 --> 06:01.690
dress up so nicely.

06:01.690 --> 06:03.060
Aren't you going to thank her?

06:03.060 --> 06:04.630
I'll thank her personally.

06:04.870 --> 06:05.640
Personally?

06:06.000 --> 06:07.510
Then should your sister also

06:07.510 --> 06:09.110
thank Mr. Xu personally?

06:09.680 --> 06:11.430
Who's pedaling?

06:11.450 --> 06:13.180
Who's holding the handlebars?

06:13.620 --> 06:15.120
Why don't you sing a song?

06:15.680 --> 06:16.140
Okay.

06:16.420 --> 06:16.860
Okay.

06:17.870 --> 06:23.140
Should auld acquaintance be forgot

06:23.190 --> 06:27.660
and never brought to mind?

06:28.040 --> 06:32.860
Should auld acquaintance be forgot.

06:29.370 --> 06:35.370
♪ Should auld acquaintance be forgot ♪

06:32.930 --> 06:37.250
And auld lang syne?

06:35.710 --> 06:41.260
♪ And never brought to mind? ♪

06:42.050 --> 06:47.670
♪ Should auld acquaintance be forgot ♪

06:48.260 --> 06:53.650
♪ And auld lang syne? ♪

06:54.830 --> 07:00.450
♪ We twa hae run about the braes ♪

07:00.900 --> 07:06.610
♪ And pou'd the gowans fine ♪

07:07.200 --> 07:12.770
♪ But we've wander'd monie a weary fit ♪

07:13.310 --> 07:19.490
♪ Sin' auld lang syne ♪

07:21.830 --> 07:22.330
Master.

07:22.430 --> 07:23.570
While you were away,

07:23.740 --> 07:24.860
I kept the house

07:24.860 --> 07:25.810
clean,

07:25.830 --> 07:27.010
tidy, and spotless.

07:27.720 --> 07:29.720
Much better than when you were here.

07:29.980 --> 07:30.390
Great.

07:30.390 --> 07:30.850
Come on.

07:31.870 --> 07:32.830
Wait a minute.

07:32.890 --> 07:35.030
You live here alone,

07:35.540 --> 07:36.750
with no one to supervise

07:36.750 --> 07:38.159
or criticize you.

07:38.810 --> 07:40.270
You must be living freely.

07:40.890 --> 07:42.000
Not at all.

07:42.060 --> 07:43.659
While you were away,

07:43.690 --> 07:45.220
I felt like the house was

07:45.720 --> 07:46.800
missing a kind of celestial aura.

07:46.800 --> 07:47.730
Celestial aura?

07:48.750 --> 07:50.680
You mean a demonic aura, don't you?

07:50.690 --> 07:53.370
A thousand-year-old demon then.

07:54.060 --> 07:55.000
Cut the chatter.

07:55.920 --> 07:57.180
A surprise inspection.

07:57.180 --> 07:59.230
Read our script.

07:59.310 --> 08:00.620
Let me see

08:00.860 --> 08:02.520
if you have made any progress.

08:02.860 --> 08:03.390
Hurry up.

08:03.430 --> 08:03.890
Okay.

08:04.250 --> 08:05.130
Then let me help you sit down.

08:05.130 --> 08:05.330
Come here.

08:05.330 --> 08:05.750
Okay.

08:05.890 --> 08:06.470
Okay.

08:06.490 --> 08:06.980
Okay.

08:08.270 --> 08:09.600
Okay.

08:09.680 --> 08:10.600
Be careful.

08:11.160 --> 08:12.060
Okay, sit down.

08:13.930 --> 08:14.300
Okay.

08:14.920 --> 08:15.680
Hurry up.

08:15.770 --> 08:16.300
Hurry up.

08:17.000 --> 08:17.930
Read the script.

08:18.270 --> 08:18.800
Hurry up.

08:23.790 --> 08:26.050
[The Late Love]
[Screenwriter: He Sheng]

08:26.870 --> 08:27.470
Hurry up.

08:28.890 --> 08:29.480
Hurry up.

08:30.270 --> 08:30.980
[The Late Love]
[Screenwriter: He Sheng]

08:31.010 --> 08:33.890
[The Late Love, Script by Xu]

08:45.270 --> 08:46.350
From now on, in the troupe,

08:45.700 --> 08:52.870
[Fenghua Song and Dance Troupe]

08:46.480 --> 08:48.340
you should learn from the other teachers.

08:48.340 --> 08:48.890
Okay.

08:48.980 --> 08:50.500
Call me if you need anything.

08:50.500 --> 08:50.890
Okay.

08:51.220 --> 08:52.080
After you go back,

08:52.080 --> 08:53.280
say hello to your dad.

08:53.770 --> 08:55.300
My dad says hello to you too.

08:55.360 --> 08:56.420
You're too polite.

08:56.440 --> 08:57.920
It's a small thing.

08:58.320 --> 08:58.730
Go now.

08:58.770 --> 08:59.370
Director.

09:00.320 --> 09:01.000
My dad said

09:01.030 --> 09:02.600
our troupe's performance
at his company last time was

09:02.600 --> 09:03.490
very successful.

09:03.490 --> 09:05.170
This is for you.

09:05.340 --> 09:06.400
You are too polite.

09:06.740 --> 09:08.470
Be sure to pass on my greetings.

09:08.670 --> 09:09.360
Thank you, Director.

09:09.360 --> 09:10.620
-Get in the car.
-Okay.

09:13.980 --> 09:14.840
Bye, Director.

09:33.120 --> 09:33.630
Master.

09:39.770 --> 09:41.740
While I was recovering

09:42.480 --> 09:44.360
in Sichuan,

09:46.080 --> 09:47.500
I never expected

09:48.630 --> 09:50.020
you to change the script

09:51.630 --> 09:53.050
like this.

09:54.200 --> 09:55.590
Didn't you tell me

09:56.010 --> 09:56.970
to be bold

09:57.290 --> 09:58.600
and go all out?

10:00.390 --> 10:01.000
You

10:02.120 --> 10:03.320
really went all out.

10:05.120 --> 10:06.250
You gave it your all.

10:07.010 --> 10:08.750
You weren't just copying.

10:10.130 --> 10:11.290
This draft

10:12.890 --> 10:14.860
is half mine

10:16.030 --> 10:17.720
and half yours.

10:18.630 --> 10:19.410
M-Master.

10:19.440 --> 10:21.850
I... I just wrote it...

10:21.940 --> 10:22.580
for fun.

10:22.580 --> 10:23.860
I read it to you...

10:23.940 --> 10:25.360
just to make you laugh.

10:25.720 --> 10:27.240
I copied the script you told me to copy.

10:27.240 --> 10:28.410
I'll read it to you now.

10:28.410 --> 10:29.550
No need.

10:30.530 --> 10:31.310
That draft

10:31.630 --> 10:32.690
has been scrapped.

10:34.010 --> 10:34.470
Come on.

10:35.550 --> 10:38.410
Bring the script here.

10:39.510 --> 10:40.610
Get a pen.

10:42.080 --> 10:42.540
Well...

10:43.000 --> 10:43.440
Hurry.

10:44.130 --> 10:45.040
Bring it here.

10:45.250 --> 10:46.300
The version

10:46.390 --> 10:47.480
you just read.

10:48.050 --> 10:48.850
Bring it here.

10:49.840 --> 10:50.900
Just bring it over!

11:03.830 --> 11:04.290
The pen.

11:10.740 --> 11:14.700
[The Late Love]

11:19.420 --> 11:22.500
[The Late Love]
[Screenwriter]

11:29.050 --> 11:34.090
[The Late Love]
[Screenwriter: He Sheng, Xu Sheng]

11:35.400 --> 11:35.910
Master!

11:35.940 --> 11:37.010
You can't do this!

11:36.070 --> 11:36.960
[Screenwriter: He Sheng, Xu Shengli]

11:37.080 --> 11:37.540
Master,

11:37.580 --> 11:38.510
being able to learn from you

11:38.510 --> 11:39.370
is already enough for me!

11:39.370 --> 11:40.940
You... you really can't do this!

11:40.940 --> 11:42.030
Bring the liquor.

11:42.600 --> 11:43.780
Get the liquor. Hurry.

11:43.780 --> 11:44.680
Hurry up!

11:44.790 --> 11:45.650
Get the liquor!

11:49.440 --> 11:49.900
Come on.

11:52.050 --> 11:52.850
Fill the cups.

11:53.740 --> 11:54.630
Fill the cups.

12:00.120 --> 12:00.580
Come on.

12:01.220 --> 12:01.770
Cheers.

12:13.480 --> 12:16.050
This is a script

12:13.550 --> 12:15.510
[The Late Love]
[Screenwriter: He Sheng, Xu Shengli]

12:17.030 --> 12:18.070
co-written by me

12:18.370 --> 12:20.580
and Xu Shengli.

12:21.620 --> 12:22.480
It's done.

12:23.890 --> 12:25.130
It's perfect!

12:28.190 --> 12:28.770
Master.

12:29.460 --> 12:29.930
Master...

12:29.930 --> 12:31.530
Master, you'll always be my teacher!

12:31.530 --> 12:32.820
No, you'll always be my master!

12:32.820 --> 12:34.220
I'll always love you!

12:34.240 --> 12:35.320
W-Wait a minute.

12:35.860 --> 12:36.590
Listen to me.

12:36.890 --> 12:39.200
I'm not your master.

12:39.870 --> 12:41.080
I'm your teacher,

12:41.750 --> 12:43.450
one of your many teachers.

12:45.170 --> 12:47.150
You have a boundless future.

12:47.960 --> 12:48.690
In this life,

12:49.460 --> 12:51.290
being your teacher

12:51.750 --> 12:54.000
makes me incredibly proud.

12:54.980 --> 12:56.300
You are my master!

13:02.130 --> 13:03.890
Be careful! Be careful!

13:03.920 --> 13:05.250
Be careful! Be careful!

13:07.130 --> 13:10.620
[Guest Room]

13:11.670 --> 13:16.570
[Guest Room]

13:13.770 --> 13:14.290
Sir.

13:14.550 --> 13:15.150
Going out?

13:15.220 --> 13:16.750
What's wrong with your leg?

13:17.030 --> 13:17.870
Nothing.

13:18.360 --> 13:20.670
I just wore a hole in this shoe
from working.

13:20.670 --> 13:22.870
Your back is bad, so don't work too much.

13:24.550 --> 13:25.810
That's heartwarming.

13:26.290 --> 13:27.260
I've got to go.

13:27.630 --> 13:28.030
Okay.

13:28.540 --> 13:33.980
[Guest Room]

13:29.480 --> 13:30.450
Come back early.

13:57.270 --> 13:57.860
Excuse me.

13:57.860 --> 13:58.890
Are you

13:58.890 --> 14:00.230
doing some performance art here?

14:00.230 --> 14:00.980
Art?

14:01.240 --> 14:02.970
I think you are quite artistic.

14:03.480 --> 14:04.700
I-I do art.

14:04.810 --> 14:08.830
[Welcome Qigong Master Cao Guangtai
for Teaching and Demonstration]

14:07.980 --> 14:09.340
Welcome...

14:11.030 --> 14:11.830
Cao Guangtai?

14:12.940 --> 14:14.940
Let yourself and nature

14:15.320 --> 14:17.650
resonate with each other

14:17.750 --> 14:19.530
in every breath.

14:17.840 --> 14:22.640
[No smoking]

14:20.370 --> 14:22.010
Exhale...

14:23.340 --> 14:25.050
Inhale...

14:27.750 --> 14:28.530
Uncle.

14:30.340 --> 14:31.020
I...

14:41.220 --> 14:41.890
Nephew.

14:43.240 --> 14:43.900
Have a seat.

14:47.170 --> 14:47.770
Thank you.

15:00.740 --> 15:03.180
Isn't it ice cold

15:03.320 --> 15:04.940
and refreshing?

15:05.500 --> 15:06.720
It's been chilled.

15:06.770 --> 15:07.900
Of course it's cold.

15:08.740 --> 15:09.620
Ice cold

15:10.200 --> 15:11.500
refers to external cold,

15:11.500 --> 15:13.960
while the cold in qi refers to
internal cold.

15:14.170 --> 15:16.230
External cold dissipates in an instant,

15:16.230 --> 15:19.100
while internal cold lingers.

15:19.170 --> 15:20.240
Uncle, why do you talk

15:20.240 --> 15:21.740
in such a rehearsed way now?

15:21.740 --> 15:22.860
And I can't hear

15:22.860 --> 15:24.240
any Shanxi accent at all.

15:24.240 --> 15:25.890
It has a bit of a Beijing accent

15:25.890 --> 15:27.690
and a hint of a Northeast accent.

15:30.000 --> 15:32.390
I'm somewhat of a wanderer,

15:32.530 --> 15:33.660
traveling all over.

15:33.820 --> 15:35.550
Especially here,

15:35.870 --> 15:38.010
if I didn't speak
with a little Beijing accent,

15:38.010 --> 15:39.600
how could I

15:39.600 --> 15:40.480
strut around?

15:41.170 --> 15:43.290
With that thick hometown accent of yours,

15:43.290 --> 15:44.770
you'd better change it soon.

15:44.770 --> 15:45.970
It'll be good for you.

15:48.220 --> 15:49.460
I never expected

15:50.440 --> 15:52.410
that we would run into each other.

15:53.700 --> 15:55.260
Aren't you a master now?

15:55.460 --> 15:57.990
Didn't you predict
that I would be in Beijing?

15:59.410 --> 16:00.360
Alright, alright.

16:00.360 --> 16:01.290
Alright, Uncle.

16:01.860 --> 16:03.050
I know

16:03.370 --> 16:05.370
you used to smash boulders on your chest
at the village entrance,

16:05.370 --> 16:06.220
and your body

16:06.240 --> 16:07.150
just couldn't take it anymore, right?

16:07.150 --> 16:08.010
I heard from my dad

16:08.010 --> 16:08.550
that you went to the Northeast

16:08.550 --> 16:09.550
to read fortunes.

16:09.840 --> 16:11.130
How come you ran over here
in the blink of an eye

16:11.130 --> 16:12.660
and became a qigong master?

16:16.170 --> 16:16.550
Uncle,

16:16.550 --> 16:17.790
you've been coughing for a while.

16:17.790 --> 16:19.920
Drink some water to catch your breath.

16:20.890 --> 16:22.510
You made me this mad.

16:33.650 --> 16:34.740
You came to Beijing

16:35.410 --> 16:36.370
to paint?

16:36.790 --> 16:37.390
What else?

16:37.440 --> 16:38.670
There's nothing else I can do.

16:38.670 --> 16:39.530
Looks like you

16:39.530 --> 16:41.930
haven't made a name for yourself painting.

16:42.440 --> 16:43.770
Tell me,

16:44.510 --> 16:45.840
how are you doing?

16:46.740 --> 16:48.910
Let's see if I can help you.

16:49.340 --> 16:50.390
We don't

16:50.860 --> 16:52.390
see each other much,

16:53.370 --> 16:55.530
but we are Caos.

16:55.890 --> 16:57.650
We have the Cao family blood.

16:58.390 --> 17:00.130
As long as you're willing to join me,

17:00.130 --> 17:02.080
I welcome you with open arms.

17:03.010 --> 17:04.329
Give it a rest, Uncle.

17:04.510 --> 17:05.589
I am a painter,

17:05.589 --> 17:06.460
an artist.

17:06.740 --> 17:07.599
You are a con...

17:11.220 --> 17:12.150
A Qigong master.

17:12.250 --> 17:13.780
We are not in the same field.

17:15.500 --> 17:17.160
You are being narrow-minded.

17:17.510 --> 17:19.750
Qigong is also an art.

17:20.030 --> 17:20.880
It does look like

17:20.880 --> 17:21.900
performance art.

17:22.240 --> 17:23.700
Go back and think about it.

17:24.380 --> 17:25.640
If you come, it is fate.

17:25.750 --> 17:27.030
If not, it is not.

17:27.480 --> 17:29.080
Okay, thanks anyway, Uncle.

17:30.030 --> 17:30.880
And remember,

17:32.270 --> 17:34.440
when you encounter things
you don't understand,

17:34.440 --> 17:35.970
don't jump to conclusions.

17:36.770 --> 17:39.050
You might get struck by lightning.

17:42.220 --> 17:43.030
Right, Uncle.

17:43.590 --> 17:44.250
About this,

17:44.400 --> 17:45.810
you should remind those who

17:45.810 --> 17:47.050
were carrying the pot on their heads.

17:47.050 --> 17:48.500
If it rains

17:48.500 --> 17:49.220
or there's lightning,

17:49.220 --> 17:50.250
don't carry it and run

17:50.250 --> 17:50.880
outside.

17:51.200 --> 17:52.050
It's a real conductor.

17:52.050 --> 17:53.090
If it attracts lightning

17:53.090 --> 17:53.830
and you get struck,

17:53.830 --> 17:55.560
it would be quite troublesome.

17:59.050 --> 17:59.710
Checkmate.

18:02.330 --> 18:02.790
Sir.

18:03.770 --> 18:05.970
Looking for Liangliang? He's not here.

18:06.380 --> 18:06.980
Take this.

18:07.850 --> 18:09.010
What is it?

18:09.590 --> 18:11.120
Take a look and you'll know.

18:12.310 --> 18:13.610
Alright. Let me see.

18:18.830 --> 18:20.030
Is it for Liangliang?

18:20.070 --> 18:21.170
It's for you.

18:21.270 --> 18:21.960
Your shoes

18:21.960 --> 18:22.980
are so worn out.

18:22.980 --> 18:23.910
Throw them away.

18:24.680 --> 18:25.810
They're for me?

18:27.220 --> 18:28.020
What? They...

18:28.140 --> 18:28.740
are for me?

18:29.270 --> 18:30.670
I don't want them.

18:31.660 --> 18:32.460
Take it.

18:32.550 --> 18:33.250
You're my uncle.

18:33.250 --> 18:34.980
What's wrong with me
buying you a pair of shoes?

18:34.980 --> 18:35.440
Well...

18:36.460 --> 18:36.860
How...

18:37.330 --> 18:38.090
how much?

18:39.590 --> 18:42.050
Not expensive.
I bought them on the way back.

18:42.610 --> 18:43.410
What's wrong?

18:43.530 --> 18:45.130
Are you not my uncle anymore?

18:45.940 --> 18:47.600
Why are you talking like that?

18:48.160 --> 18:48.810
Ranran,

18:49.070 --> 18:50.630
next time

18:50.660 --> 18:51.550
if you want to buy something
on the way again,

18:51.550 --> 18:52.310
think of...

18:53.350 --> 18:53.680
Okay.

18:53.810 --> 18:55.210
What do you want?

18:55.550 --> 18:57.510
I like jeans.

18:58.000 --> 19:00.200
How could you take advantage like that?

19:00.200 --> 19:00.580
Okay.

19:00.610 --> 19:01.980
I'll buy you a pair when I get my pay.

19:01.980 --> 19:02.400
No, no.

19:02.590 --> 19:03.400
I was kidding.

19:03.500 --> 19:05.160
I was kidding with her.

19:05.270 --> 19:05.770
Come on.

19:05.810 --> 19:06.400
I'm not like you,

19:06.400 --> 19:07.440
holding a new pair of shoes

19:07.440 --> 19:09.380
and completely forgetting
the real business.

19:09.380 --> 19:09.780
Right.

19:09.900 --> 19:11.430
I was just about to find you.

19:11.770 --> 19:13.170
Ranran, do you know

19:13.330 --> 19:15.030
what's going on with Liangliang
these days?

19:15.030 --> 19:16.360
Did you two have a fight?

19:18.980 --> 19:20.200
We didn't.

19:20.460 --> 19:21.980
Then why is it that every day
when he comes back,

19:21.980 --> 19:23.030
he slams things around

19:23.030 --> 19:24.640
or just goes straight to the bed

19:24.640 --> 19:25.700
without saying a word?

19:25.700 --> 19:27.110
It's been 3 days.

19:31.290 --> 19:31.850
He

19:32.530 --> 19:35.500
has been in a bad mood recently.

19:36.770 --> 19:38.550
But as for what exactly it is,

19:39.420 --> 19:41.480
he might be more willing to tell you.

19:46.480 --> 19:47.830
I have to go back

19:47.830 --> 19:48.640
to memorize lines

19:48.640 --> 19:49.550
and read the script.

19:49.550 --> 19:50.900
If these shoes pinch,

19:50.900 --> 19:51.530
tell me immediately

19:51.530 --> 19:52.940
so I can exchange them for you.

19:52.940 --> 19:53.740
Thank you.

19:54.570 --> 19:56.300
Come to me if you need anything.

19:58.310 --> 19:59.250
Rest early.

20:00.960 --> 20:01.610
This kid.

20:02.030 --> 20:02.830
She's so nice.

20:03.140 --> 20:04.070
Such a good girl.

20:05.610 --> 20:06.570
Didn't you say kid?

20:06.570 --> 20:07.480
That works too.

20:13.750 --> 20:14.240
Get up.

20:15.570 --> 20:16.770
We are playing chess.

20:17.810 --> 20:19.280
You're quite something.

20:19.590 --> 20:20.810
You haven't said a word for 3 days,

20:20.810 --> 20:23.010
and when you did, you just said "get up."

20:34.400 --> 20:35.130
Liangliang.

20:35.940 --> 20:36.980
Look.

20:37.810 --> 20:39.110
These are the new shoes

20:39.110 --> 20:40.450
Ranran gave me.

20:42.750 --> 20:43.880
They are so good.

20:46.900 --> 20:47.380
Cao,

20:47.920 --> 20:50.120
what did Ranran say she'd give you?

20:50.240 --> 20:50.870
Jeans.

20:51.200 --> 20:52.010
And she said she'd get me

20:52.010 --> 20:53.010
a pair of brand name ones.

20:53.010 --> 20:54.800
Lee or something.

20:54.920 --> 20:56.120
Lee Cooper.

20:56.250 --> 20:57.450
Yes, that's the name.

20:57.850 --> 20:59.680
That's a famous brand.

20:59.680 --> 21:00.140
Right?

21:00.590 --> 21:01.350
This girl Ranran,

21:01.350 --> 21:02.420
she really is nice.

21:02.480 --> 21:03.370
She really is.

21:03.400 --> 21:05.510
She just takes pity on me.

21:05.510 --> 21:06.010
You?

21:06.070 --> 21:07.880
I'd say she takes pity on me.

21:07.880 --> 21:10.080
What do you two have to be pitiful about?

21:10.400 --> 21:11.930
Who are you trying to annoy?

21:12.050 --> 21:13.460
What are you putting on a show for?

21:13.460 --> 21:14.900
Who's annoying who?

21:15.510 --> 21:16.250
And you weren't putting on a show?

21:16.250 --> 21:17.460
You've been acting all pitiful for days.

21:17.460 --> 21:19.090
Are you in a drama or something?

21:19.090 --> 21:20.350
You've been like this

21:20.350 --> 21:21.030
for 3 days.

21:21.030 --> 21:22.110
Who are you acting for?

21:22.110 --> 21:22.590
What?

21:22.640 --> 21:23.460
The young master
from Beijing is acting like

21:23.460 --> 21:24.380
it's hard when it's really not, isn't he?

21:24.380 --> 21:26.220
What's wrong with being from Beijing?

21:26.220 --> 21:28.080
What advantage does that give us?

21:32.420 --> 21:33.330
I thought

21:34.330 --> 21:37.260
I didn't get into
that song and dance troupe last time

21:37.350 --> 21:39.010
because I wasn't good enough.

21:39.290 --> 21:40.380
I was thinking of saving money

21:40.380 --> 21:42.400
to get a teacher to improve my skills.

21:42.400 --> 21:44.380
But I didn't expect it
to be an inside job.

21:44.380 --> 21:46.500
It has nothing to do with ability at all.

21:46.500 --> 21:48.290
I just like playing the saxophone.

21:48.290 --> 21:49.260
I asked around

21:49.290 --> 21:50.790
how to get into this circle.

21:50.790 --> 21:51.570
They told me

21:52.920 --> 21:54.440
you need connections.

21:54.550 --> 21:56.080
Once you have connections,

21:56.880 --> 21:58.540
you can find a stepping stone.

21:59.380 --> 22:02.040
How much do you think
this stepping stone costs?

22:03.510 --> 22:05.060
I play in underpasses.

22:05.090 --> 22:06.190
I play in bars.

22:06.250 --> 22:07.880
When will I ever be able to afford

22:07.880 --> 22:08.610
this stone?

22:11.960 --> 22:13.830
What's wrong with being from Beijing?

22:13.830 --> 22:14.770
You guys are always going on

22:14.770 --> 22:16.370
about me being from Beijing.

22:25.480 --> 22:25.980
I know.

22:27.680 --> 22:28.980
You can't go home.

22:30.130 --> 22:32.050
But this is your home too.

22:34.420 --> 22:35.150
Don't you...

22:35.960 --> 22:37.180
have us?

22:38.250 --> 22:39.350
Why are you crying?

22:43.880 --> 22:45.010
Well, you know...

22:46.050 --> 22:47.240
I would have spent it

22:48.550 --> 22:50.610
if it weren't for being 10 yuan short.

22:58.500 --> 22:59.760
That's all my savings.

23:00.830 --> 23:02.690
You have to buy me a meal every day.

23:07.400 --> 23:08.330
Take it. Take it.

23:08.440 --> 23:08.770
Here.

23:16.740 --> 23:18.070
What if I take this money

23:23.090 --> 23:24.420
and it doesn't work out?

23:28.850 --> 23:30.110
Just consider it lost.

23:31.090 --> 23:31.550
Anyway,

23:32.650 --> 23:34.050
we've lost money before.

23:34.290 --> 23:36.030
Just consider it blown away by the wind.

23:36.030 --> 23:37.030
Yeah, blown away.

23:45.010 --> 23:46.790
D-Don't feel bad anymore.

23:49.810 --> 23:52.010
I'll come back to try on the shoes later.

24:06.200 --> 24:06.570
Director,

24:06.570 --> 24:08.430
what's the studio's opinion now?

24:09.110 --> 24:09.960
Are there some parts in the script

24:09.960 --> 24:10.570
that

24:10.610 --> 24:12.010
they didn't understand?

24:13.460 --> 24:14.400
Director,

24:15.240 --> 24:16.250
just tell me.

24:16.310 --> 24:17.030
Your sighing

24:17.030 --> 24:18.240
makes my heart sink.

24:20.090 --> 24:20.660
Xu.

24:22.440 --> 24:24.300
I'm not trying to discourage you.

24:24.590 --> 24:26.090
But there are some situations

24:26.090 --> 24:28.020
that I must explain to you clearly.

24:29.250 --> 24:30.980
These opinions from the studio

24:31.750 --> 24:32.950
are just a formality.

24:33.830 --> 24:34.500
Which means

24:34.550 --> 24:36.310
the studio is not going to film it.

24:36.310 --> 24:37.450
Wh-Why is that?

24:37.850 --> 24:38.830
Kid, kid.

24:40.880 --> 24:41.810
Some things

24:42.960 --> 24:44.160
are about the people,

24:44.440 --> 24:45.640
not the script.

24:46.110 --> 24:47.370
What about this movie?

24:49.920 --> 24:51.090
It's such a great story,

24:51.090 --> 24:52.250
and it was personally produced

24:52.250 --> 24:53.410
by you and Mr. He.

24:53.660 --> 24:54.790
So that's it?

24:55.350 --> 24:56.410
It can't be filmed?

24:58.530 --> 24:59.860
Let's not talk about me.

25:00.200 --> 25:01.400
Mr. He spent so many years

25:01.400 --> 25:02.530
writing this story.

25:03.920 --> 25:05.420
Now that his eyes are like this,

25:05.420 --> 25:06.160
when will he be able to write

25:06.160 --> 25:07.130
his next story?

25:07.380 --> 25:08.350
Or will he even

25:08.400 --> 25:09.400
have a next story?

25:11.400 --> 25:12.260
They say...

25:12.790 --> 25:14.250
scripts are our children.

25:14.610 --> 25:14.990
Well,

25:15.510 --> 25:16.250
every child

25:16.270 --> 25:17.470
has a different fate.

25:20.350 --> 25:21.200
Sometimes,

25:21.610 --> 25:23.610
the encounters and partings in life

25:24.700 --> 25:26.610
just require patient waiting.

25:30.920 --> 25:31.920
I won't change it!

25:32.500 --> 25:33.910
Not a single word.

25:34.400 --> 25:35.420
It's an art film,

25:35.500 --> 25:37.900
and they have to turn it
into a commercial one.

25:37.900 --> 25:39.050
It's so weird.

25:40.250 --> 25:41.250
It's ridiculous!

25:41.980 --> 25:42.710
Ridiculous!

25:52.400 --> 25:55.040
From the day I became a screenwriter

25:55.610 --> 25:57.470
and wrote my first word until now,

25:58.140 --> 25:59.200
it's been 36 years.

26:01.010 --> 26:01.610
I know

26:02.500 --> 26:04.030
that for every word I write,

26:04.810 --> 26:07.610
there's always someone
who might have an opinion.

26:08.940 --> 26:10.850
But the scripts I write

26:11.530 --> 26:13.090
are like my own children.

26:13.680 --> 26:14.900
If someone

26:14.960 --> 26:16.220
broke their legs

26:16.850 --> 26:18.310
and gouged out their eyes,

26:19.420 --> 26:20.480
would that be okay?

26:20.530 --> 26:21.000
No.

26:24.220 --> 26:25.090
Some scripts

26:26.530 --> 26:28.980
are like the girl in my heart

26:29.420 --> 26:31.220
with beautiful single eyelids.

26:33.350 --> 26:35.590
If you ask her to change her makeup

26:36.720 --> 26:38.740
and make her cheeks bright red,

26:39.610 --> 26:40.340
is that okay?

26:41.220 --> 26:41.680
Yes.

26:43.680 --> 26:45.810
But if they take her away

26:49.140 --> 26:51.140
and give her double eyelid surgery,

26:51.790 --> 26:52.920
can you tolerate it?

26:53.330 --> 26:54.010
No!

26:55.110 --> 26:55.690
Exactly.

26:56.290 --> 26:56.660
Master,

26:56.660 --> 26:58.050
but this is your hard work.

26:58.050 --> 26:59.590
It's your hard work too!

27:10.350 --> 27:13.460
There's 10,000 yuan on the desk.

27:14.740 --> 27:15.570
Take it.

27:17.310 --> 27:18.090
I'm used

27:18.880 --> 27:20.620
to being alone.

27:21.850 --> 27:23.310
I don't need to save money.

27:24.160 --> 27:25.090
Just consider it

27:25.750 --> 27:27.080
as your manuscript fee.

27:28.000 --> 27:29.330
I can't take this money.

27:29.550 --> 27:31.250
You need money for your medical treatment.

27:31.250 --> 27:32.050
Stop nagging!

27:36.680 --> 27:37.340
From now on,

27:38.720 --> 27:39.360
we

27:39.940 --> 27:41.400
will go our separate ways.

27:42.940 --> 27:45.920
I have a few words to say to you.

27:48.310 --> 27:50.880
Don't complain to others.

27:52.420 --> 27:55.460
Don't tell others
that you're having a hard time.

27:56.590 --> 27:59.010
Don't glorify a tragedy.

28:00.400 --> 28:02.220
Do you remember the movie

28:03.030 --> 28:05.250
"Lenin in 1918"?

28:06.900 --> 28:09.140
Moscow was running out of food.

28:10.070 --> 28:12.090
Lenin asked Vasily to bring some.

28:13.740 --> 28:16.420
Vasily narrowly escaped death

28:17.090 --> 28:18.950
and delivered the food to Moscow.

28:20.000 --> 28:20.830
Lenin said,

28:22.000 --> 28:23.000
"Comrade Vasily,

28:24.110 --> 28:24.750
I heard

28:25.290 --> 28:26.420
you were surrounded

28:27.680 --> 28:29.480
and went through many battles."

28:31.270 --> 28:32.330
Vasily replied...

28:34.740 --> 28:35.670
Vasily replied,

28:39.030 --> 28:40.360
"That was inevitable!"

28:40.740 --> 28:41.290
Right.

28:43.820 --> 28:44.940
Just one sentence—

28:45.850 --> 28:47.380
"That was inevitable."

28:49.440 --> 28:50.610
In this world,

28:51.400 --> 28:55.720
many things are inevitable.

28:58.270 --> 29:01.660
What we can do is

29:03.330 --> 29:05.770
protect what we want,

29:07.700 --> 29:10.220
shoulder what we can bear,

29:12.160 --> 29:15.610
and keep moving forward.

29:13.920 --> 29:20.390
[The Late Love]
[Screenwriter: He Sheng, Xu Shengli]

29:38.530 --> 29:39.060
Shengli!

29:39.830 --> 29:40.620
Xu Shengli!

29:41.000 --> 29:41.730
You're back?

29:43.090 --> 29:44.020
Perfect timing.

29:44.330 --> 29:45.250
What is this?

29:45.720 --> 29:46.500
Didn't you ask my mom

29:46.500 --> 29:47.740
about tailoring?

29:48.220 --> 29:48.900
These are

29:48.960 --> 29:50.700
books and magazines she collected.

29:50.700 --> 29:51.230
And this.

29:52.110 --> 29:53.570
These are fabric samples.

29:54.110 --> 29:55.640
The content is really rich.

29:55.810 --> 29:57.070
See if you can use them.

30:03.000 --> 30:04.260
What's that reaction?

30:06.140 --> 30:07.460
I was thinking I should call your mom

30:07.460 --> 30:08.740
to thank her.

30:09.680 --> 30:10.940
Being beautiful and kindhearted

30:10.940 --> 30:12.420
is indeed hereditary.

30:12.720 --> 30:13.770
You are so sweet.

30:15.220 --> 30:17.550
Let me tell you
another piece of good news.

30:17.980 --> 30:18.770
The singing competition

30:18.770 --> 30:20.050
has started its preliminaries.

30:20.050 --> 30:21.000
I'm about to start recording

30:21.000 --> 30:21.750
my tape.

30:22.500 --> 30:23.240
That's great news.

30:23.240 --> 30:24.440
It's wonderful news.

30:24.480 --> 30:25.310
Well... then...

30:25.310 --> 30:26.610
Is there anything I can help you with?

30:26.610 --> 30:29.010
No need.
Just focus on writing your script.

30:30.770 --> 30:32.770
It feels colder these past few days.

30:33.550 --> 30:35.250
Autumn in Beijing is really short.

30:35.250 --> 30:36.530
Winter is coming soon.

30:38.330 --> 30:39.370
Then let's wait

30:39.500 --> 30:40.860
for the next spring together.

30:40.860 --> 30:44.120
[Seasons Change Hostel]

30:59.280 --> 31:01.840
[The Late Love]
[Screenwriter: He Sheng, Xu Shengli]

31:30.660 --> 31:32.980
Send 5,000 back home.

31:36.460 --> 31:38.240
Zhuang Zhuang's tuition fee.

31:54.230 --> 32:02.080
[The Late Love]
[Screenwriter: He Sheng, Xu Shengli]

32:04.220 --> 32:07.610
[Guest Room]

32:10.520 --> 32:12.050
Morning, Northeasterner.

32:12.220 --> 32:13.080
Zhuang Zhuang.

32:13.140 --> 32:13.940
Wait a minute.

32:20.050 --> 32:20.850
What's wrong?

32:26.260 --> 32:30.690
[The Late Love]
[Screenwriter: He Sheng, Xu Shengli]

32:31.400 --> 32:32.260
What happened?

32:34.010 --> 32:34.810
Xu

32:35.030 --> 32:36.700
spent most of last night alone

32:36.880 --> 32:37.840
on the rooftop.

32:38.270 --> 32:39.180
I picked them all back

32:39.180 --> 32:39.980
from the trash can for him.

32:39.980 --> 32:41.310
They should all be here.

32:44.010 --> 32:45.400
It's been so long.

32:46.050 --> 32:46.770
Xu has been struggling with

32:46.770 --> 32:47.940
this script every day.

32:47.750 --> 32:50.800
[The Late Love]
[Screenwriter: He Sheng, Xu Shengli]

32:48.460 --> 32:49.970
But now he tore it all up.

32:50.680 --> 32:51.460
I don't think

32:51.480 --> 32:53.340
I can tell anyone else about this,

32:53.790 --> 32:55.720
so I had no choice but to come to you.

33:03.090 --> 33:04.090
Northeasterner.

33:05.570 --> 33:06.700
Let's just keep this

33:07.050 --> 33:08.250
between the two of us.

33:08.750 --> 33:09.880
Don't worry. I know.

33:10.420 --> 33:12.680
This is a basic principle of being human.

33:15.350 --> 33:16.810
Where are you going today?

33:17.240 --> 33:18.840
I'm here to see you off.

33:19.440 --> 33:21.640
Aren't you busy with the script lately?

33:21.980 --> 33:23.280
It's alright. Well...

33:23.350 --> 33:24.330
Mr. He told me to come

33:24.330 --> 33:25.530
and experience life.

33:26.090 --> 33:27.000
Isn't the script

33:27.000 --> 33:28.260
in its final stage now?

33:28.270 --> 33:30.090
He said he would write the rest himself.

33:30.090 --> 33:31.620
He told me to come and relax.

33:37.110 --> 33:37.670
Alright.

33:37.940 --> 33:39.280
My office is just ahead.

33:39.310 --> 33:40.880
You don't need to walk me any further.

33:40.880 --> 33:41.210
Okay.

33:43.750 --> 33:44.640
So... if...

33:44.690 --> 33:46.940
you're not too busy
with the script lately,

33:46.940 --> 33:48.200
could you do me a favor?

33:48.750 --> 33:49.410
What favor?

33:49.770 --> 33:51.030
I'm too busy with work.

33:51.030 --> 33:51.960
Recording the tape

33:51.960 --> 33:53.420
is too much for one person.

33:53.700 --> 33:54.800
No problem.

33:54.830 --> 33:55.660
Although I don't know how to do it,

33:55.660 --> 33:56.590
you can teach me.

33:56.850 --> 33:58.180
I'll be your assistant.

33:58.380 --> 33:58.910
Alright.

33:59.380 --> 34:00.510
Thanks.

34:00.900 --> 34:02.480
No need to be so polite with me.

34:02.480 --> 34:03.540
I'll be going then.

34:03.740 --> 34:04.270
Alright.

34:04.530 --> 34:05.060
Bye-bye.

34:21.400 --> 34:21.980
Toby.

34:22.510 --> 34:23.150
What's wrong?

34:23.150 --> 34:24.780
Zhuang Zhuang, I was just looking for you.

34:24.780 --> 34:26.050
The tiger is back from abroad.

34:26.050 --> 34:26.800
Did you do the research

34:26.800 --> 34:27.440
I told you to do?

34:27.440 --> 34:28.120
I did.

34:28.530 --> 34:29.880
I also found several references.

34:29.880 --> 34:30.570
Are these enough?

34:30.570 --> 34:31.030
Okay.

34:31.300 --> 34:32.690
Improvise when the time comes.

34:32.690 --> 34:33.570
Coffee, coffee.

34:33.570 --> 34:35.050
Do you know the Great Wall Hotel?

34:35.050 --> 34:35.820
I've heard of it.

34:35.820 --> 34:37.020
Okay, go buy a coffee.

34:37.070 --> 34:37.630
Hand-ground.

34:37.630 --> 34:38.760
No condensed milk, no sugar.

34:38.760 --> 34:39.510
Give me the stuff.

34:39.510 --> 34:39.909
Go now!

34:41.880 --> 34:43.480
No condensed milk, no sugar.

35:05.000 --> 35:06.130
The design of these sleeves

35:06.130 --> 35:07.070
is quite unique.

35:07.920 --> 35:09.210
What were you thinking?

35:09.210 --> 35:09.780
Ms. Yue?

35:10.030 --> 35:10.840
Ms. Yue,

35:11.300 --> 35:12.230
I was thinking

35:12.260 --> 35:13.860
of making the sleeves longer

35:13.860 --> 35:15.090
and more flowy.

35:17.820 --> 35:19.110
With sleeves this heavy,

35:19.110 --> 35:20.630
you'd build your biceps.

35:23.690 --> 35:24.850
And what is this?

35:25.030 --> 35:25.980
Ms. Yue,

35:26.480 --> 35:27.740
this is a magpie.

35:31.440 --> 35:32.640
It really is a magpie.

35:33.110 --> 35:36.110
Did you get into the art academy
through connections?

35:40.430 --> 35:41.070
Tracy,

35:41.690 --> 35:42.750
where are you from?

35:43.590 --> 35:44.900
I think you can

35:45.300 --> 35:46.320
wear this dress at your wedding

35:46.320 --> 35:47.250
in your village.

35:48.210 --> 35:48.840
Not bad.

35:50.050 --> 35:51.150
Your Group 1

35:51.150 --> 35:52.280
has very good taste.

35:52.420 --> 35:53.000
These are the clothes

35:53.000 --> 35:53.980
you spent a month

35:54.010 --> 35:55.280
designing,

35:55.300 --> 35:55.710
right?

35:56.550 --> 35:57.750
I'm sorry, Ms. Yue...

35:59.260 --> 36:00.060
Little mouth—

36:04.170 --> 36:04.820
Lucy.

36:04.980 --> 36:06.040
She's calling you.

36:06.860 --> 36:07.190
Me?

36:07.230 --> 36:07.980
Lucy.

36:08.340 --> 36:08.900
Coffee.

36:10.050 --> 36:10.750
Ms. Yue,

36:10.880 --> 36:12.010
here's your coffee.

36:12.380 --> 36:13.650
I was afraid it would get cold,

36:13.650 --> 36:15.380
so I bought a thermos on the way.

36:18.440 --> 36:18.940
Ms. Yue.

36:20.630 --> 36:21.300
Ms. Yue, well...

36:21.300 --> 36:23.050
our Group 2
has also found some references.

36:23.050 --> 36:25.250
Zhuang Zhuang, please introduce them.

36:25.650 --> 36:26.210
Ms. Yue...

36:26.210 --> 36:27.050
Skip Group 2.

36:27.860 --> 36:29.280
Raise your lifestyle aesthetics

36:29.280 --> 36:30.440
to the company's entry-level standard,

36:30.440 --> 36:31.570
and then we'll talk.

36:40.400 --> 36:41.980
Was I blind?

36:42.500 --> 36:43.980
Was I blind

36:44.070 --> 36:45.320
to hire you, a bunch of losers,

36:45.320 --> 36:46.000
into the company,

36:46.000 --> 36:46.880
just to have you design

36:46.880 --> 36:47.780
this kind of trash for me?

36:47.780 --> 36:49.000
Jonathan is coming

36:49.000 --> 36:50.030
to see the samples in a few days.

36:50.030 --> 36:51.360
See the samples. Got it?

36:55.550 --> 36:57.480
Figure out a solution yourselves.

37:03.960 --> 37:05.160
You'll get used to it.

37:15.810 --> 37:16.440
Toby.

37:26.760 --> 37:27.960
Just now... Sit down.

37:28.980 --> 37:30.180
Sorry about just now.

37:30.500 --> 37:31.550
If I hadn't dealt with it

37:31.550 --> 37:32.250
in time,

37:32.510 --> 37:34.340
she would have scolded everyone again.

37:34.340 --> 37:35.670
Keep this for yourself.

37:36.150 --> 37:36.750
Thank you.

37:38.070 --> 37:39.280
I should be sorry.

37:39.510 --> 37:40.480
I should have

37:40.500 --> 37:41.840
prepared the coffee earlier

37:41.840 --> 37:43.300
and put it in Ms. Yue's cup.

37:43.420 --> 37:44.950
I'll know better next time.

37:45.780 --> 37:47.240
You've got a good mindset.

37:47.440 --> 37:49.370
You didn't get discouraged at all.

37:49.550 --> 37:51.340
That's just how she talks.

37:51.900 --> 37:53.130
But if you stay here long enough,

37:53.130 --> 37:54.530
you'll definitely grow.

37:54.960 --> 37:56.130
When I first came here,

37:56.130 --> 37:57.930
I cried every day when I got home.

37:59.860 --> 38:00.460
Oh, right.

38:01.820 --> 38:02.420
Lucy...

38:02.730 --> 38:03.570
Who is Lucy?

38:04.360 --> 38:06.560
Did Ms. Yue mistake me for someone else?

38:06.690 --> 38:08.420
I forgot to tell you about that.

38:10.090 --> 38:10.710
Here,

38:10.780 --> 38:12.580
as long as you're her assistant,

38:12.730 --> 38:13.860
you're called Lucy.

38:14.210 --> 38:16.300
The head of Group 1 is called Tracy.

38:16.730 --> 38:18.590
The head of Group 2 is called Toby.

38:19.280 --> 38:20.820
She thinks it's easier to remember.

38:20.820 --> 38:22.350
Just treat it as a job title.

38:23.190 --> 38:23.720
Alright.

38:25.780 --> 38:27.280
So... is there anything else

38:27.280 --> 38:28.280
I can do right now?

38:28.320 --> 38:29.530
Looks like we're on a very tight deadline

38:29.530 --> 38:30.500
for our design drafts.

38:30.500 --> 38:31.650
But I don't know

38:31.670 --> 38:33.530
whether I should submit them now.

38:35.670 --> 38:37.090
Our boss

38:37.170 --> 38:38.170
is just like this.

38:38.690 --> 38:40.210
She said she wouldn't look at them today,

38:40.210 --> 38:42.090
but tomorrow she might want to see them.

38:42.090 --> 38:43.530
She may say she doesn't like you today,

38:43.530 --> 38:45.670
but she could really like you tomorrow.

38:45.670 --> 38:47.400
She's totally unpredictable.

38:48.510 --> 38:50.660
Anyway, just keep them ready.

38:50.730 --> 38:51.360
If there's anything you don't understand,

38:51.360 --> 38:52.020
just ask me.

38:52.400 --> 38:53.880
If you really don't dare to submit them,

38:53.880 --> 38:54.800
I'll do it for you.

38:54.800 --> 38:55.150
Okay.

38:56.460 --> 38:57.320
Oh right, Toby.

38:59.150 --> 39:00.410
What is your real name?

39:01.980 --> 39:04.910
You should use your real name
outside of work, right?

39:05.300 --> 39:05.860
Well...

39:12.150 --> 39:13.280
My name is Li Daqing.

39:16.280 --> 39:16.630
Dad,

39:16.860 --> 39:17.620
I'm back.

39:19.150 --> 39:19.880
Liangliang.

39:20.630 --> 39:21.560
Where is Ranran?

39:22.800 --> 39:24.600
She can't come over all the time.

39:25.440 --> 39:26.240
Red bean buns.

39:26.320 --> 39:27.210
Your mom made them.

39:27.210 --> 39:28.340
Take them to Ranran.

39:28.510 --> 39:29.340
Why aren't you two

39:29.340 --> 39:30.840
this nice to me?

39:32.820 --> 39:33.610
You are not allowed to play

39:33.610 --> 39:35.130
those noisy tunes later. You hear me?

39:35.130 --> 39:35.840
Okay.

39:36.510 --> 39:37.530
I'll play a gentle one for you.

39:37.530 --> 39:37.930
You...

39:44.630 --> 39:46.690
Do you think we can get the money back?

39:55.920 --> 39:57.280
Who allowed you to play here?

39:57.280 --> 39:58.090
Stop playing!

39:58.360 --> 39:58.820
Your spit

39:58.820 --> 40:00.080
splashed into my bowl!

40:01.070 --> 40:01.670
I'm sorry.

40:01.730 --> 40:03.590
I'll get you a fresh plate of this.

40:04.090 --> 40:05.340
You think one plate of food
is enough to brush us off,

40:05.340 --> 40:05.880
right?

40:08.030 --> 40:09.400
What the hell were you playing?

40:09.400 --> 40:10.010
Let me see.

40:10.610 --> 40:11.470
Don't touch it.

40:11.480 --> 40:12.340
Why are you touching it?

40:12.340 --> 40:13.220
What's with the attitude?

40:13.220 --> 40:14.320
I'll smash it!

40:14.340 --> 40:16.260
Don't touch my stuff!

40:16.860 --> 40:17.400
How dare you hit him?

40:17.400 --> 40:18.610
You lousy busker!

40:18.760 --> 40:20.010
Trying to pick a fight with us?

40:20.010 --> 40:20.690
Wait a minute.

40:20.690 --> 40:22.290
Let me take off my saxophone.

40:22.460 --> 40:23.050
Screw you!

40:23.050 --> 40:23.650
Screw you!

40:27.380 --> 40:28.640
Still wanna act tough?

40:32.360 --> 40:33.550
You little brat!

40:37.400 --> 40:38.210
Take that!

40:49.670 --> 40:50.400
What is this?

40:52.400 --> 40:53.130
What is this?

40:53.760 --> 40:54.170
An instrument.

40:54.170 --> 40:55.170
What instrument?

40:55.440 --> 40:56.820
A... A saxophone.

40:57.000 --> 40:58.150
A saxophone!

40:58.260 --> 40:59.170
It's not a piece of junk

40:59.170 --> 40:59.970
like you said!

41:00.840 --> 41:01.470
Also!

41:01.860 --> 41:02.720
What does he do?

41:04.110 --> 41:06.970
He is a saxophone artist!

41:07.170 --> 41:08.380
He's not a lousy busker

41:08.380 --> 41:09.370
like you said!

41:11.420 --> 41:11.960
Get out!

41:12.670 --> 41:14.270
You don't deserve to listen!

41:14.500 --> 41:15.210
Get lost!

41:20.480 --> 41:21.010
Get out!

41:44.590 --> 41:45.050
Dad.

41:59.900 --> 42:03.590
[Beijing Cuisine]

42:02.500 --> 42:03.360
Thank you, Dad.

42:08.440 --> 42:09.380
Is that how a son

42:09.420 --> 42:10.610
talks to his father?

42:15.030 --> 42:17.290
It was my first time seeing you like this.

42:17.460 --> 42:18.510
I've never seen it before.

42:18.510 --> 42:19.530
You brat.

42:20.230 --> 42:21.180
Remember this.

42:23.090 --> 42:24.690
I, Tao Baohua, am the only one

42:25.230 --> 42:26.590
allowed to hit my son.

42:27.880 --> 42:28.540
Nobody else

42:29.650 --> 42:31.130
can lay a finger on you.

42:42.300 --> 42:43.900
Should I come back tomorrow?

42:44.440 --> 42:45.070
Of course.

42:46.260 --> 42:47.480
Why shouldn't you?

42:47.740 --> 42:57.280
[Opening Time: 5:30 a.m.]

42:49.150 --> 42:50.810
If I come back a few more times,

42:51.280 --> 42:52.650
our family business

42:53.400 --> 42:54.510
will be ruined by me.
